n class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/25/03 3:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Frustrated</span><hr size=1> Hecate shook her head.  She couldn't believe how her kin could be so nearsighted, maybe it was due to all the inbreeding.  Didn't they know that what she sought to do benefited them as well?  Why were they so complacent?  Has being a deity dulled their senses, blunted them from the wonders of life, pushed them to seek annihilation?<br>
<br>
It was sad in a sense, so many of them seemed to want to give up their godhood.  If that was the case, then so be it, there was only so much she could or would do for them.  Leave them to their fate then, as long as they didn't stand in her way, she wasn't going to waste any more time upon them.<br>
<br>
::Persephone, I understand you think I have lost my mind.  Trust me, I am far from senility.  In fact, I see things quite clearly.  And it saddens me to see so many of you choosing to go the other way.  I came here today to seek  a future for myself.  None of this concerns you or any one else.  When I succeed, maybe then it will clear your minds, and show you what bounty awaits all of you.  But if you choose not to, that is your decision, not mine.  Just stay out of my way.  I ask this of you, and anyone else who is thinking of diswaying me.  Choose carefully, for what we do today affects not only us, but a myriad of other gods and goddesses.  You could be sealing the fate of all of us.<br>
<br>
Hecate spins around, and walks down one of the hallways.  As she walks away, she says quietly over her shoulder, but loud enough for them to hear.<br>
<br>
::Our lives are forever entertwined, and we will surely cross paths many many times again.  What I do here, I do for myself.  I hold no animosity to any of you.  But please stay out of my way.  You can either join me or leave me in peace.<br>
<br>
With that, Hecate fades away, proceeding onwards to her destination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixlordhadesxi>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/25/03 4:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Stalemate</span><hr size=1> ::Hades watched the actions occur. He felts the subliminal messages and knew exactly who and where they came from...Hypnos. He also felt the presence of his wife, Persephone. He placed his arm around her, as she spoke to those present::<br>
